        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>The who:</strong>
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #06266d;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-23-jul-25-foundations-h1-12-deng-xiaoping?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >Deng Xiaoping</a
            >
            was the leader of China from 1978 to 1992. He abandoned orthodox
            communist doctrines and incorporated elements of the open market
            system. He managed to preserve the communist regime while improving
            China‚Äôs geopolitical position. Xiaoping believed that societies need
            an effective bureaucracy, whether military or private, to establish
            and maintain a market.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>The achievement:</strong> His most significant achievement
            was the economic reform program, which enabled businesses to operate
            in special economic zones and welcomed foreign funds. He
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #06266d;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-23-jul-25-foundations-h1-13-proposed-rotating-leadership?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >proposed rotating leadership</a
            >
            and the generational theory of government, which allows each
            generation a turn to lead the country.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            Under his leadership, China experienced rapid growth, rising
            standards of living, expanded
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #06266d;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-23-jul-25-foundations-h1-14-personal-and-cultural-liberties?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >personal and cultural liberties</a
            >, and strengthened ties to the global economy.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>The criticism:</strong> While he opened up China to the
            international market, he sustained crackdowns on internal dissent.
            He applied a strict one-party rule and opposed political
            liberalization. His most controversial decision was the approval of
            the
            <a
              style="
                text-decoration: none;
                border-bottom: 2px solid #06266d;
                color: black;
              "
              href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-23-jul-25-foundations-h1-15-1989-tiananmen-square-protests?source=website"
              target="_blank"
              >1989 Tiananmen Square protests</a
            >
            takedown. Despite the economic growth, there was an even wider
            inconsistency in monetary equality.
          </p>
